Pour the @water{220%ml} for the bulgur into a #large saucepan{}, stir in half of the
@chicken stock paste{20%g} and bring to the boil.

Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%g}, bring back up to the boil and simmer for
~{1%minute}.

Pop a lid on the pan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for
~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, fry the @British beef mince{240%g}, ~{5-6%minutes}. Break up the mince
as it cooks, then drain the fat.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after
handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Add the @curry powder mix{1%sachet}. Fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir in the @Rogan Josh curry paste{50%g}, @tomato passata{1%carton},
@water{50%ml} for the sauce and the remaining chicken stock paste.

Bring up to a boil, then lower to a simmer.

Stir through the @peas{120%g} and cook for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Fluff up the bulgur and share between bowls.

Stir the @honey{1%tbsp} into the beef.

Top with your beef rogan josh.

Dollop over the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g}.

Enjoy!